<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-04T12:55:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-04T12:55:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/60: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-04T20:30:00+02:35">May 4, 1936—8:30
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 4—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>284. Many thanks for your 180 and 181.<note n="25" xml:id="d283fn25">Neither printed.</note> Hope the Department is not unduly
                                alarmed but we would so much like to save the Legation if at all
                                possible.</p>
                            <p>Reference your 182, inter-Legation radio communications were being
                                arranged but unexpectedly sudden outbreak of disturbances prevented
                                completion.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>